	<Title>
		Did you exercise today? Reward yourself!
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;After you exercise, take a few minutes to sit down and relax. Reflect on what you&apos;ve just accomplished. Savor the good feelings that exercise gives you. This type of internal reward can help you make a long-term commitment to regular exercise. External rewards can help, too. When you reach a longer range goal, treat yourself to a new pair of walking shoes or new tunes to enjoy while you exercise.&lt;/p&gt;
